/*
  Sleep() is a function that causes the program to pause for a specified duration of time.
  
  Inside the parenthesis, you define the time to wait.  NOTE:  This value is in milliseconds  
  (1000 = 1sec , 500 = 0.5sec , so on so forth)
  
  You will need to include a preprocessor directive, as shown below.
*/


PREPROCESSOR DIRECTIVE
----------------------
#include <windows.h>


-=+=-


CODE:

Sleep(1000);  //change 1000 to any other number to change the amount ot time to pause.




